represented 15 days of life/thousand persons. The ratio of years of potential 
life lost to number of deaths was on average 30 years per death. The estimated 
financial impact amounted to R$ 22.9 million in non-earned wages. 
Hospitalization costs totaled R$ 831.5 thousand. Estimated days of wages lost 
per admission period (median: 6 days) amounted to R$ 103.0 thousand.
CONCLUSIONS: There was a high social cost in terms of years of potential life 
lost and partial hospital costs associated with leptospirosis when compared to 
the possibility of early treatment or prevention of infection, both of which 
could minimize the impact of the disease on the Brazilian population.

